14 September 2014 Last updated at 00:51 BST 
Prime Minister David Cameron has described the murder of David Haines by Islamic State as an &quot;act of pure evil&quot;.
The Foreign Office said it was &quot;working urgently to verify&quot; the video and was offering support to Mr Haines's family.
The 44-year-old aid worker was kidnapped in Syria last year.
Andy Moore reports.
 